The paper deals with the problem of objective quality assessment of in-the-wild videos, which involves computer vision (CV) and multimedia (MM) techniques. The proposed method uses a deep neural network, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (AI) and machine learning (ML) in computer science (CS). The paper also mentions the use of gated recurrent units, which are commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) and time-series analysis, falling under the categories of CS.LG and CS.IT. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.MM, followed by cs.AI, cs.LG, and cs.IT.
